  +===================================================================+

  You are logged in as analyst on 'station' — an offline crypto workstation.

  Two jobs. First, break an intercepted classic cipher (challenge.txt) and
  see why simple substitution is hopeless against a computer. Then use real
  GnuPG (PGP) the way it's used in the wild: Alice and Bob exchange a message
  only the recipient can read, and a signature that proves who sent it.

  Mission: learn what makes encryption weak, and what a key actually protects.

    >  type  labhelp   for the mission and the commands you'll need
    >  everything here is real — real cipher tool, real GnuPG; try things,
       break things, and feel free to ask an AI assistant to explain anything

